'Cool' 's the best, its got that breezy vibe - that synth riff that starts from the beginning of the song which carries to the end, oh man, it makes you feel like youre having a carefree summer day, and you can forget about everything that's been happening so far. Dua's vocals are exceptionally strong and prominent throughout the song and so is not overshadowed by the electronic sound. It manages to sound like a modern pop song and yet also bring out the nostalgic 2000s dance-pop song sound at the same time, I can hear 'cool' drawing inspiration from that era like from Gwen Stefani for example, and these influences adds the cherry on top of this already splendid song!
